.TH SUTURE-BATCH "1" "April 2026" "Suture v5.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
suture\-batch \- Batch operations for managing multiple files or clients
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B suture batch [\\fIoptions\\fR] \\fIcommand\\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
Batch operations for managing multiple files or clients.
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
.B stage
Stage files matching a pattern
.TP
.B commit
Commit files matching a pattern
.TP
.B export\-clients
Export multiple clients at once
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \\\-C \\fI<REPO_PATH>\\fR
Run as if suture was started in <path>
.TP
.BR \\\-h, \\\-\\\-help
Print help
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR suture (1)
